## Add records
```js
// The add method receives an array value, and can create multiple records at the same time, and a single request can create up to 10 records
datasheet.records.create({{ records }}).then(response => {
  if (response.success) {
    console.log(response.data);
  } else {
    console.error(response);
  }
})
```

### Returned data example

```json
{{ response }}
```


### Other parameters and tips

The add interface receives an array value that can create multiple records simultaneously, up to 10 records per request

